**who —** BELOW PLANCK — a techne sphere — the art

**what —** There is a smallest length at which our physics still makes sense — the Planck length, about 1.6 × 10⁻³⁵ metres. Below it, general relativity and quantum mechanics contradict each other, and the very idea of 'distance' may dissolve. We have no confirmed theory of what is down there. This sphere draws that honestly: not a structure, but a refusal — static that never becomes an image.

